# Feature Implementation Request: Role-Based Authentication & Course Assignment System

You are working on an existing academic report generation system built with React + Express + SQLite + Sequelize + Python processing scripts.

Your task is to refactor the authentication and user management system into a role-based architecture while preserving all existing report generation functionality.

## IMPORTANT RULES

1. Do NOT modify any report generation logic.
2. Do NOT modify Python processing scripts.
3. Do NOT modify attainment calculations.
4. Do NOT modify report generation workflows.
5. All changes must be backward-compatible with existing course/report data.
6. Focus only on authentication, authorization, faculty management, course assignment, and report submission workflows.

---

# TARGET ARCHITECTURE

## Roles

The system must support two roles:

### Admin

Permissions:

* Login
* Create faculty accounts
* Edit faculty accounts
* Activate/deactivate faculty accounts
* Create courses
* Edit courses
* Assign courses to faculty
* View all generated reports
* View all submitted reports
* Track report status
* Monitor faculty activity

### Faculty

Permissions:

* Login
* View only assigned courses
* Upload marks
* Generate reports
* Submit generated reports to admin
* View own submitted reports
* Change password
* Change display name
* View profile

Faculty CANNOT:

* Create courses
* Edit courses
* Assign courses
* View other faculty data
* View reports belonging to other faculty
* Change email address

---

# AUTHENTICATION SYSTEM

Replace the existing authentication system with:

## Login Page

Single login page:

Fields:

* Email
* Password

Authentication flow:

1. User enters email and password.
2. System validates credentials.
3. System determines role.
4. Redirect based on role.

Faculty:

/faculty/dashboard

Admin:

/admin/dashboard

Use JWT authentication.

Store passwords securely using bcrypt.

Do NOT store plain-text passwords.

